subject: Scandinavian Nature Poetry (Late 19th century)
permalink: /Scandinavian Nature Poetry (Late 19th century)/Gottfrid Kallstenius/Gottfrid Kallstenius - Nights Echo
---

The echo of the owl's call,
Cuts through the velvet hush of night,
A forgotten song of the wild,
Resonating through the trees.

In the moon's soft glow, I linger,
Captivated by nature's mystery,
Each star, a reminder of magic,
In the quiet of the world unseen.


- Gottfrid Kallstenius
